                                                °phala smṛtaḥ \msCaacorr, °pradaḥ smṛtaḥ \Ed}

                 \footnote{6cd ŁSee e.g.\ \BhP\ 6.9.6: $ brahmahatyām añjalinā jagrāha yad apīśvaraḥ|

                                    saṃvatsarānte tad aghaṃ bhūtānāṃ sa viśuddhaye|

                                    bhūmyambudrumayoṣidbhyaś caturdhā vyabhajad dhariḥ||</PARAL>

                 \footnote{Context: Viśvarūpa was a son of Tvaṣṭṛ. Viśvarūpa's heads were struck off by Indra. 
                         In the Bhāgavatapurāṇa, Indra's sin are distributed among the ground, 
                         water, trees and women.}

